dont want to negotiate or compromise or even talk about 
compromise he said but in the house the ability to strike a 
wise compromise is an essential part of leadership 
there has to be an understanding he said that there are times 
that subtle maneuvers can succeed where a frontal attack will almost 
certainly fail 
most members of the house he said dont want their leaders 
sending them into unwinnable battles 
members of the house and their leaders in particular are the 
nations most exposed national politicians closest to the people 
up for reelection every two years both ears always open to the 
sound of social and economic change michel says 
we dont have four years like a president or six years like a 
senator to hide our mistakes michel said we serve as a kind of 
distant earlywarning system for democracy we are ever aware of new 
problems 
and we are also aware of the clumsy legislative means at our 
disposal to deal with those problems he said 
