the republic of azerbaijan where rival ethnic groups have carried 
out violent protests pravda said today 
also today armenian leaders traveled to moscow to appeal to the 
kremlin for help in breaking what they say is an economic blockade 
by neighboring azerbaijan that is strangling their economy armenian 
sources said 
the communist party daily said the blast occurred near the 
central azerbaijani town of evlakh on saturday the bomb exploded 
about six hours after the bus left tbilisi the capital of the 
georgian republic for the azerbaijani capital baku 
who planted the bomb and how its still difficult to say 
azerbaijan assistant interior minister akif rafiyev told pravda the 
device was placed under a window seat in the bus pravda said 
among those killed was a baby pravda said twentyseven people 
were hurt including five who are in critical condition the report 
said 
rafiyev said the casualty toll could have been much higher had 
not the driver escaped injury and prevented the bus from crashing 
into a ravine 
official reports so far have not said whether the blast is linked 
to ethnic tension in the caucasus mountain region of the soviet 
south 
azerbaijan is engaged in a bitter dispute with neighboring 
armenia for control of the nagornokarabakh region that region 
while legally part of azerbaijan is predominantly armenian the 
armenian population demands that the region be taken from azerbaijan 
and annexed to armenia 
about 100 people have been killed and hundreds of thousands of 
people have fled their homes in violence that has encompassed both 
of the republics during the past 18 months moscow has imposed 
direct rule on nagornokarabakh in an effort to ease tensions 
armenian leaders say they are under virtual economic blockade 
from neighboring azerbaijan more than 80 percent of the shipments 
armenia receives from other parts of the soviet union are shipped by 
rail from azerbaijan 
rem ananikyan an editor of the official armenpress news agency 
in yerevan the armenian capital said in a telephone interview 
today that the republics leadership would take blockade issue to a 
full session of the communist party central committee scheduled to 
begin tuesday 
the central committee meeting will be devoted to finding a way to 
solve a plethora of ethnic disputes in the soviet unions 15 
republics which include more than 100 ethnic groups 
party leaders from around the country including armenian party 
chief suren arutyunyan and azerbaijan leader abdulrakhman vezirov 
will attend 
theres no salt theres no sugar theres no oil ananikyan 
said when asked about supplies in yerevan stores the grapes are 
staying in the field the vegetables are not being harvested because 
theres no fuel 
the official soviet press has reported that even ambulances are 
at a standstill because there is no fuel 
the armenian supreme soviet or legislature met in an emergency 
session saturday and sunday to discuss the slowdown in supplies from 
azerbaijan 
armenian officials say builders in northern armenia who are 
reconstructing cities leveled by an earthquake last dec 7 are out 
of supplies that means many people may be without shelter as winter 
approaches they say 
azerbaijans parliament reasserted its right to rule 
nagornokarabakh on saturday calling the district an integral part 
of the republic and noting the soviet constitution classifies it as 
such 
