plant where coal is cleaned sorted and shipped management 
people are over there in the area evaluating the situation 
when they entered the plant sunday the demonstrators said they 
were protesting stalled contract talks and court actions since they 
went on strike against pittston on april 5 
the demonstrators said they had enough provisions to last several 
weeks and they issued a statement saying they wanted their actions 
to remain peaceful 
the strike began when about 1700 miners from virginia and west 
virginia walked off their jobs at pittston operations and there has 
been no resumption set for talks aimed at ending the walkout after 
negotiations broke off last week umw officials said they would wait 
for pittston to schedule the next round of discussions 
