<TEXT>
the commerce department announced today the 
united states is prepared to provide hungary with a wide series of 
business and economic benefits including permanent 
mostfavorednation trade status 
it would make hungary the first eastern european nation having 
such status since enactment of the jacksonvanik amendment in 1974 
tying those benefits to free emigration policies the department 
said yugoslavia and poland also have mfn status but obtained 
theirs before 1974 
in addition commerce secretary robert a mosbacher said the 
united states is prepared to improve tariff treatment of hungarian 
products extend development programs and create a 25 million fund 
to help create private business in the marxist country 
this step is an important part of implementing president bushs 
goal of building an american partnership with hungary mosbacher 
said in a statement following a meeting with hungarian trade 
minister tamas beck in budapest a copy was made available here 
such an agreement is fundamental for private sector business 
because it would contain investment protection gauartees which boost 
confidence and open the way to substantially increased us private 
investment in hungary mosbacher said 
he said beck agreed to open negotiations on the proposals 
mosbacher said the proposals include granting hungary permanent 
mostfavorednation trade status in october if the hungarian 
parliament as expected enacts legislation on freedom of emigration 
by the end of september 
such status assures that exports to the united states will not 
face discriminatory tariffs hungary now receives such benefits only 
on a yeartoyear basis 
mosbacher also said the plan calls for extending generalized 
system of preferences treatment that would offer hungarian exporters 
dutyfree tariff treatment for a broad range of exports to the 
united states 
the commerce secretary said bush also has submitted to congress 
legislation to extend overseas private investment corp programs to 
hungary and create a 256 million private enterprise fund 
opic programs would provide investment guarantees to us 
companies investing in hungary and the enterprise fund would help 
establish of private business there 
</TEXT>
