<TEXT>
george bush has finally broken with ronald 
reagan the issue trees 
where reagan saw trees as a pervasive polluter of the atmosphere 
his successor praises them as the oldest cheapest and most 
efficient air purifier on earth 
reagan said nine years ago that more atmospheric contamination 
was caused by natural processes than manmade pollution but bush 
declared monday that its tree planting time for america and for 
all of spaceship earth 
reagan contended during the 1980 presidential campaign that trees 
were responsible for 93 percent of the nitrogen oxides in the 
atmosphere environmentalists said reagan confused nitrous oxide 
which comes from decaying plant matter and isnt harmful with 
nitrogen oxide a pollutant emitted by coal plants 
the theory prompted reagan press secretary james brady who was 
in the campaign plane as it flew over a burning forest to shout in 
jest killer trees killer trees 
bush came down on the side of environmentalists in a speech in 
sioux falls sd inviting his audience to join the greening of 
america 
trees he said can reduce the heat of a summers day quiet a 
highways noise feed the hungry provide shelter from the wind and 
warmth in the winter 
every tree he said is a compact between generations 
all true says neil sampson a vice president of the american 
forestry association 
weve got a tremendous opportunity to affect the environment 
with trees and that can start for many people right around their 
house he said this is not rocket science it doesnt take new 
technology it doesnt cause us to go to heroic investments 
it isnt going to cure the whole world either but at least 
its a start of doing something positive we know how to do it 
today weve got the money to do it and we have people who know how 
to do it 
the plant a tree idea comes late 
since the first europeans set foot on americas shores about 300 
million acres of forests have disappeared to build cities and 
provide land for fields and roads 
of the 2 billion acres that make up the united states 737 
million acres are forest sampson said 
he suggested cities are the place to start planting trees 
most cities are under a heat island effect they are four 
degrees warmer than the suburbs and that seems to be rising by one 
degree per decade he said for each degree of heat we power 
consumers in washington pay an extra 10000 an hour 
in the process of growing wood trees take in carbon dioxide 
the stuff we exhale convert it into cellulose and breathe out 
oxygen they also act like huge coolers by evaporating water which 
absorbs heat as it moves from liquid to a vapor 
bush challenged south dakotans to pledge to plant 100 million 
trees by 2000 something north dakotans already have promised to do 
sampson said his group has been urging 100 million new trees too 
but around homes and businesses under a program called global 
releaf 
he said that los angeles a year before the city was to be the 
site of the 1984 olympics planted 1 million trees air pollution 
experts believe that was the single most costeffective way to 
improve air quality sampson said 
houston is aiming for 2 million trees by the turn of the century 
he said 
in his speech bush mentioned that the white house grounds have 
an elm planted by john quincy adams southern magnolias brought 
andrew jackson and oaks planted by dwight d eisenhower 
he didnt mention that for his seal adams used the latin words 
alteri seculo taken from the phrase he plants trees to 
benefit another generation 
