<TEXT>
here are some important dates in the history of jordan 
191618 emir hussein bin ali of mecca and his sons revolt 
against turkish rule during world war i with the aid of britain 
which promises them a vast postwar arab kingdom 
1920 britain reneges on promises and cuts up the area with the 
french in a postwar mandate the french expel emir husseins son 
feisal as king of syria british later make him king of iraq 
feisals brother abdullah arrives in what later becomes jordan 
1921 britain separates the new emirate of transjordan from the 
ottoman territories of syria hejaz and palestine and persuades a 
reluctant abdullah to become emir of the british protectorate on a 
sixmonth trial basis 
1937 abdullah is the only major arab leader to endorse a call 
for partitioning palestine into jewish and arab sectors the arab 
sector to be ruled by transjordan 
1946 transjordan gains independence from britain with abdullah 
as king 
1948 abdullahs britishled arab legion joins the war against 
newly established israel and holds onto the west bank and east 
jerusalem with the new territories the kingdom changes its name to 
jordan in 1950 palestinian refugees flood country 
1951 abdullah is assassinated by disgruntled palestinian 
nationalists and his son talal takes the throne 
1952 talal abdicates because of mental illness and the throne 
passes to abdullahs grandson the 17yearold hussein who takes up 
power in 1953 after reaching his 18th birthday by the islamic 
calendar 
1956 hussein expels british military officers holds free 
elections leftist sentiment sweeps the arab world as israel 
britain and france attack egypt in the suez war 
1957 hussein squashes a leftist coup and bans political parties 
1958 husseins cousin king faisal is assassinated in a 
leftist coup in iraq british troops help protect jordan 
1967 hussein joins egypt and syria in the war against israel 
and loses the west bank and east jerusalem more than 200000 
palestinian refugees flood the kingdom hussein imposes martial law 
1970 husseins army crushes palestinian guerrillas who had 
threatened his throne during fighting that became known as black 
september the army also beats back a syrian invasion 
1973 jordan sends a token force to help syria in the fourth 
arabisraeli war 
1974 the arab league recognizes the palestine liberation 
organization as sole representative of the palestinians hussein 
responds by suspending parliament half of which represents west 
bank palestinians 
1978 jordan left out of ussponsored egyptisrael peace 
talks rejects the resulting camp david peace accords and joins an 
arab boycott of egypt arguing against separate settlements 
198385 hussein unsuccessfully tries to bring the united states 
and plo together for peace effort with israel 
198687 jordan launches a west bank development plan tacitly 
supported by israel that challenges the plo role on the west bank 
it collapses when proplo rioting breaks out in jordan in november 
1987 
1988 hussein renounces sovereignty over the west bank in favor 
of the plo and encourages the organization to accept us conditions 
for talks he insists he will never negotiate on behalf of 
palestinians he suspends parliament 
1989 four days of riots over economic problems sweep jordan 
hussein changes the government and calls elections for a new 
parliament 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

