hes the king willis said his comic timing was superb 
even in films that didnt do so well like arsenic and old lace i 
could never figure how he did it 
willis admired grants resourcefulness the way he gently 
manipulated the other characters in such classics as the 
philadelphia story and the awful truth he tried to use the 
same techniques in moonlighting playing off the straightlaced 
cybill shepherd 
i always thought if you could make somebody laugh you could 
get them off balance and if you could get them off balance you 
could get what you want from them he said 
while moonlighting drew on the snappy dialogue of grants 
