be limited to 68 percent with a modest improvement in 1991 and a 
strong rise by 1992 
under the plan first pennsylvania bank na would become an 
operating subsidiary of corestates retaining its name as have 
corestates three existing full service banks philadelphia 
national hamilton and new jersey national 
philadelphia national and first pennsylvania banks would be 
realigned to serve specific market segments in the philadelphia 
area first pennsylvania would serve primarily the retail and 
smallbusiness market while philadelphia national would focus on 
wholesale commercial markets 
