ford motor co the leading lighttruck seller for 
three consecutive years is steering clear of comparing its models 
with the competitors trucks in its new advertising company 
officials said monday 
ford and chevrolet trucks have been battling for sales supremacy 
for years and chevrolet ran a series of ads last year comparing its 
trucks with fords in tugs of war load hauling and switching to 
fourwheeldrive in something chevrolet tagged the ditch of doom 
john vanderzee advertising manager for the ford division said 
monday the company wont trade pot shots using chevys in its 1990 
commercials 
in one ad for 1990 a heavy chain is locked to the bumper of a 
hefty ford fourwheel drive pickup the truck begins to pull and an 
announcer talks about engine size power and competition 
the truck at the other end of the chain pulling equally hard 
also is a ford rather than a competitor and the announcer voices 
the theme the toughest competition we have is ourselves 
one of the fundamental principles of advertising is when you 
are the marketing leader you never mention the competition 
vanderzee said 
ford research indicates potential buyers want facts not staged 
competitions he said 
the consumers really believe these socalled stunts are not 
what they want vanderzee said we would like to think the 
competition is going to get off their kick of taking us on 
chevrolet however is continuing its comparison ads for 1990 
chevrolet sold more than 13 million light trucks compared with 
fords total of more than 12 million in 1985 but ford has led in 
succeeding years 
in 1986 ford sold nearly 14 million trucks while chevrolet sold 
more than 12 million in 1987 ford sold more than 14 million 
versus fewer than 12 million for chevrolet and in 1988 ford sold 
more than 15 million trucks to more than 13 million for chevrolet 
according to fords figures 
although fords truck ads are keeping the gloves on the 
companys car ads arent there are pointed comparisons to features 
and prices of competitors models in television advertisements for 
escort festiva and tempo cars 
two new vehicle introductions will boost fords advertising 
budget for 1990 vanderzee said though he wouldnt give an overall 
figure or a percentage increase 
